$ Python standard library: html
@ html

{ escape #py-html-escape

  By default, single quotes are escaped to `#x27;`:
  -
 `html.escape("foo'bar&baz")` -> `foo&#x27;bar&amp;baz`

  If the second parameter is set to `False`, single quotes are not escaped:
  -
 `html.escape("foo'bar&baz", False)` -> `foo'bar&amp;baz`

}
{ unescape #py-html-unescape

 `html.unescape('foo&amp;bar')` -> `foo&bar`

}

